Yea the reel is late and long, I’m a 90’s mom. @leannepelosi 

What a container you ladies created @sistersummit_ . So grateful for the opportunity to speak on so many topics dear to me and the opportunity to support, connect, reconnect, play, and go deep with so many fine as women in snow sports. 

We celebrated and howled at the moon for our beloved leader @hilareenelson 

Finally met so many of my e-crushes. 
Yew, I love women.

We really are better together.

There are so many more magical little moments that exist outside this reel, but it was frigid and this is what I got.

Massive thanks to everyone at @mustangpowder !!!

More than a few times this season when l've been asked "Are you doing The Approach, again?" | find myself searching for some answer that conveys how fully and resounding of a "YES—of course" it is for me, and for us. A YES that is as obvious and big as the mountains of work that still need to be done in this industry. The Approach Again? YES, because Inclusivity isn't a trend. We will continue to share our journey until this space begins to look like the world we inhabit and is SAFE for us to occupy. Are we there yet? Not even close. We still at The Approach.

This has not always been the easiest project to find the money for, we only know how to dream big. Endless thanks to partners like @subaru_usa who are committed to a better world and believe in making big dreams come true.

#outbackwilderness

Thank you,Japan— for being just what I needed. A much welcomed slow down and change of pace. And to the friends seen and unseen in this video, this bag of memories will be with me forever. A lucky girl in her lucky era. 

Many more moments to drop.

Thank you @burton

——the places your passion will take you. Where do you want to take your love?

@miraecampbell

Fam just got way bigger. Thing is when you’re in this place you don’t need so many words. No explaining, no performing, just ease. Black joy beaming.✨
#burtoncultureshifters

and to the Carpenter family @burton @fattire @redbull @aspensnowmass @zacharynigro @waddellchelsea among many others who put in the money and sweat to make it real.

Suck at sharing—great at living.

So grateful to @roarkwomens @roark for making this dream trip possible. On the road moving through the world sight unseen is my happy place. Bonus is getting to do it with such a bunch of dope human beans. 

Massive gratitude to the real and unseen forces that aligned to make it possible.

@miraecampbell 🎞️
In nature, disturbance is as important as peace.

Between fossil fuels and human power—let’s be honest mostly dino fuel— I’ve been able to play in and witness some otherworldly natural landscapes. It fills me with momentous guilt. It’s one of my primary blocks when it comes to sharing what I’m up to. Even with all the education, you sit in an uncomfortable amount of knowledge and awareness.  And no amount of school sends you off with the answers.

Knowing that your athletic pursuits and lifestyle carries a detrimental impact on the world is a real tension. Still, I know being outside and moving beyond what’s comfortable makes us human. 

With the support of @athleticbrewing I put out a lil 2cents about some things we can do to build up our personal environmentalism. Given it’s not a feasible option for most of us to opt out of the system we are in, we can begin in our own way by supporting good work. 

I was happy to do partner with @AthleticBrewing a non-alcoholic beer B- Corp that puts energy and money behind several initiatives like Two for the trails where for every product purchased, 2% of sales up to $2M to protecting and restoring local trails. And donating 1% of revenue to grant recipients and 501c3s. Link in my bio. 

#AthleticBrewing
#TwoForTheTrails

Sponsored by Athletic Brewing. Milford, CT and San Diego, CA. Near Beer.

When I took these shots during our @thule shoot at Retallack last year, I didn’t expect the frames to double and triple expose as they did.

I love these shots, certainly not for their clarity but how they translate the general feeling of the trip.

Life is like that though. Moments stack, blend and blur until all you’re left with is a hodge podge of memories distilled down to a sentiment. What do we ever remember wholly clearly except for how we’re left feeling?

So grateful to be apart of the @thule family and the opportunity to be apart of such warmth and creativity. Now the once top secret #thuleepos is launched. A demonstration of what Thule and Swedes do best—design. A universal bike carrier that folds for storage and carry. I love it and you bike heads will too. 

#bringyourlife
#bringyourbike
#thuleadventure

Roughly a year ago today I headed back home from Denali. 

Embarked on that expedition with 5 strangers self guided. It was difficult and we didn’t end up summitting, but I can’t say I really remember the bitter moments all that much. Mostly just the sweetness. Celebrating birthdays, contemplating motherhood, laughing dancing, nightly hot water bottles in the sleeping bag, no service, mistaking seracs for planes overhead, the best bowel movements happen when you’re moving everyday. 

Now @staywild is back up there 
@jaimesomers belly companion is now out in the world. 
Who knows what the rest of us are up to. @_zakmills @tailergray @parkinglotpoacher 

That’s the beauty of expeditions, you come together in an intimate container for a short while and once again blast back into the world absorbed in our own ways.

Think I’m ready for the next one. 

Thanks to the sponsors who made it happen
@fattire @smartwool @patagonia_snow

Grandma says it’s three generations.

Thanks as always for an incredible session @thealchemistress .. such a treat.

A summer for the books in Wyoming. 

So grateful for the slowed pace to take it in and spend time with friends, new and old, in a place that matters most to me. It’s refreshed my environmental perspective and released some cynicism.  I can’t wait to share what’s coming. 

In the meantime, if you’re looking for ways to reinvigorate your own relationship to the environment and your agency, check my piece I worked on with @athleticbrewing, link in my bio.

Slightest chill in the air.

This camera feels like my brain, not sure I should fix it.

Without record memories become one and none.
Signs of life. Birthdays, late nights, new years, being afraid to die, being cared for. Excited for the living ahead.
